2. ERROR SPOTTING - THE GOLDEN PATTERNS
These 10 errors appear in 70% of questions:

Subject-Verb mismatch with "one of"
One of the boys are → is ❌
Preposition errors (wrong preposition 90% of time)
Different than → from ❌
Married with → to ❌
Article errors (a/an/the confusion)
The Jupiter → Jupiter ❌
Tense consistency (mixing past/present)
He said man was mortal → is ❌
Redundancy (double negatives/words)
Return back → return ❌
Reflexive pronouns misuse
I enjoyed myself → enjoyed ❌
Comparison errors
More better → better ❌
Parallelism (structure mismatch)
He likes to swim and dancing ❌
Pronoun-antecedent mismatch
Each student must bring their books → his/her ❌
