He speaks good → well ❌
PRO TIP: In exam, scan for these 10 patterns first in every error spotting question!

3. CLOZE TEST - THE WINNING FORMULA
DON'T read word by word! Use this method:

STEP 1: Read the ENTIRE passage first (30 seconds) - understand the theme STEP 2: Read again and fill ONLY the blanks you're 100% sure about STEP 3: For tough blanks, use these clues:

Grammar Clues (60% answers):

Look at word before/after blank
"... interested ___ sports" → IN (preposition pattern)
"He ___ to school" → WENT (subject-verb-time agreement)
Context Clues (30% answers):

Positive or negative tone?
"Despite hardships, he remained ___" → OPTIMISTIC (positive tone)
Collocation Clues (10% answers):

Common word pairs
"make a ___" → DECISION/CHOICE
"pay ___" → ATTENTION
GOLDEN RULE: Never leave a cloze blank empty - even educated guess has 25% chance!

