These are PURE FORMULA questions - NO thinking needed!

Voice Formula:

Active: Subject + Verb + Object
Passive: Object + be + V3 + by + Subject
Common Traps:

Preposition stays with verb: "laugh AT" → "be laughed AT"
Two objects: Give both options
He taught me English → I was taught English / English was taught to me
Narration Formula:

Said to → told
Said → said that
Question → asked
Command → ordered/requested
Common Traps:

Universal truth = NO tense change
"Let" sentence: Let + object + be + V3 + by us
